line_1: And can make a good Pudding, and cut out a Shirt.
line_2: She has Wisdom enough, that keeps out of the Dirt,

line_1: Would change his living oftener than his shirt;
line_2: Old Evremond, renown'd for wit and dirt,

line_1: Another quits his stockings, breeches, shirt,
line_2: Because he fancies virtue dwells with dirt:
